Separately, and as a non-binding courtesy request, the author would
appreciate the following from anyone who finds this work useful:

  1. CITATION. If you incorporate this software into research, products,
     services, or accessibility work, please consider citing it. A
     CITATION.cff file is provided at the repository root and is
     surfaced by GitHub as a "Cite this repository" link.

  2. WRITTEN ACKNOWLEDGMENT ON REQUEST. If the author contacts you in
     writing to ask for a brief acknowledgment of how you have used,
     adapted, or built on this software, please consider sending one.
     The aim is to demonstrate the impact and adoption of
     accessibility-first developer tooling — currently underrepresented
     in the developer-tools field — to funders, employers, and the
     broader software community.

These requests reflect the author's preference. They are not legally
enforceable through this license, and a downstream user is fully within
their rights under the MIT terms above to ignore them. The author offers
this work as software that anyone can use, modify, and redistribute under
those terms; the courtesy requests are a separate channel for collegial
exchange when impact reporting matters.
